Text:"sin that hath no equal,
So fast to bar the gate!"},{ID:3,
Text:"O Jesus, Thou art pleading
In accents meek and low,
\"I died for you, my children,
And will ye treat me so?\""},{ID:4,
Text:"Lord, with shame and sorrow
We open now the door:
Dear Saviour, enter, enter,
Abide forever more! Amen."},{ID:34,
Text:"V7. WHEREVER HE LEADS I'LL GO"},{ID:35,
Text:"I. 'Take up thy cross and follow Me,\"
I heard my Master say;
\"I gave my life to ransom thee,
Surrender your all today.\"
Wherever He leads I'll go...
Wherever He leads I'll go,..
I'll follow my Christ, who loves me so,
Wherever he leads I'll go."},{ID:2,
Text:"He drew me closer to his side,
I sought his will to know,
And in that will I now abide,
Wherever he leadth I'll go."},{ID:3,
Text:"It may be through the shadows dim,
Or O'er the stormy sea,
I take my cross and fellow him,
Wherever he leadth me."},{ID:2,
Text:"He drew me closer to His
side, I sought His will to
k:.ow, And in that willi
now abide, Wherever He
leads I'll go."},{ID:3,
Text:"It may be through the
shadows dim, Or o'er the
stormy sea,
I take my cross and follow
Him, Wherever He leadeth
me."},{ID:2,
Text:"He drew me closer to His
side, I sought His will to
k:.ow, And in that willi
now abide, Wherever He
leads I'll go."},{ID:3,
Text:"It may be through the
shadows dim, Or o'er the
stormy sea,
I take my cross and follow
Him, Wherever He leadeth
me."},{ID:4,
Text:"My heart, my life, my all bring
To Christ who loves me so;
He is my Master, Lord, and King,
Wherever He leads I'll go."},{ID:34,
Text:"V8. LET OTHERS SEE JESUS IN YOU"},{ID:35,
Text:"I. While passing this' this world of sin,
And others your life shall view,
Be clean and pure without, within,
Let others see Jesus in you.
Let others see Jesus in you,
Let others see Jesus in you;
Keep telling the story, be faithful and true,
Let others see Jesus in you."},{ID:2,
Text:"Your life's a book before their eyes,
They're reading it thro' and thro';
Say, does it point them to the skies,
Do others see Jesus in you?"},{ID:3,
Text:"What joy 'twill be at set of sun,
In mansions beyond the blue,
To find some souls that you have won;
Let others see Jesus in you."},{ID:4,
Text:"Then live for Christ both day and night,
Be faithful, be brave and true,
And lead the lost to life and light;
Let others see Jesus in you."},{ID:349,
Text:"I AM THINE, 0 LORD"},{ID:350,
Text:"I. I am Thine, 0 Lord; I have heard thy voice,
And it told Thy love to me;
But I long to rise in the arms of faith,
And be closer drawn to Thee.
Draw me nearer, nearer, nearer, blessed Lord,
To the cross where Thou hast died;
Draw me nearer, nearer, nearer, blessed Lord,
To Thy precious, bleeding side."},{ID:2,
Text:"Consecrate me now to thy service, Lord,
By the pow'r of grace divine;
Let my soul look up with a stead fast hope,
And my will be lost in Thine."},{ID:3,
Text:"O the pure delight of a single hour
That before Thy throne I spend;
When I kneel in pray'r, and with Thee, my God,
I commune as friend with friend!"},{ID:4,
Text:"There are depths of love that I cannot know
Till I cross the narrow sea;
There are heights of joy that I may not reach
Till I rest in peace with Thee."},{ID:350,
Text:"IS YOUR ALL ON THE ALTAR?"},{
Text:"You have longed for sweet peace,' and for faith to increase,
And have earnestly, fervently prayed;
But you cannot have rest or be perfectly blest
Until all on the altar is laid.
Is your all on the altar of sacrifice laid?
Your heart, does the Spirit control?
You can only be blest and have peace and sweet rest,
As you yield Him your body and soul."},{ID:2,
Text:"Would you walk with the Lord in the light of His Word,
And have peace and contentment always;
You must do His sweet will to be free from all ill.
On the altar your all you must lay."},{ID:3,
Text:"Oh, we never can know what the Lord will bestow
Of the blessings for which we have prayed,
Till our body and soul He doth fully control,
And our all on the altar is laid."},{ID:4,
Text:"Who can tell all the love He will send from above,
And how happy our hearts will be made,
Of the fellowship sweet we shall share at His feet,
When our all on the altar is laid."},{ID:35,
Text:"V1. \"ARE YE ABLE,\" SAID THE MASTER"},{ID:36,
Text:"I. \"Are ye able,\" said the master,
'To be crucified with me?\"
\"Yea,\" the sturdy dreamers answered,
\"To the death we follow Thee.\"
\"Lord, we are able, .. Our spirits are Thine,
Remold them, make us like Thee, divine:
Thy guiding radiance above us shall be
A beacon to God, to faith and loyalty."},{ID:2,
Text:"\"Are ye able?\" still the Master
Whispers down eternity,
And heroic spirits answer,
Now, as then in Galilee,"},{ID:352,
Text:"LIVING FOR JESUS"},{ID:353,
Text:"I. Living for Jesus a life that is true,
Striving to please Him in all that I do,
Yielding allegiance, glad hearted and free,
This is the pathway of blessing for me.
O Jesus, Lord and Saviour,
I give myself to Thee;
For Thou, in Thine atonement,
Didst give thyself for me;
I own no other Master,
My heart shall be Thy throne;
My life I give, henceforth to live,
O Christ, for Thee alone."},{ID:2,
Text:"Living for Jesus who died in my place,
Bearing on Calv'ry my sin and I disgrace,
Such love constrains me to answer His call,
Follow His leading and give.
Him my all."},{ID:3,
Text:"Living for Jesus thro' earth's little while,
My dearest treasure, the light of His smile,
Seeking the lost ones He died to redeem,
Bringing the weary to find rest in Him."},{ID:35,
Text:"V3. GIVE OF YOUR BEST TO THE MASTER"},{ID:36,
Text:"I. Give of your best to the Master,
Give of the strength of your youth;
Throw your soul's fresh, glowing ardor
Into the battle for truth:
Jesus has set the example,
Dauntless was He, young and brave;
Give Him your loyal devotion,
Give Him the best that you have.
Give of your best to the Master,
Give of the strength of your youth
Clad in salvation s full armor,
Join in the battle for truth."},{ID:2,
Text:"Give of your best to the Master
Give Him first place in your heart;
Give Him first place in your service,
Consecrate ev'ry part:
Give, and to you shall be given,
God His beloved Son gave;
Gratefully seeking to serve Him,
Give Him the best that you have."},{ID:3,
Text:"Give of your best to the Master,
Naught else is worthy His love;
'He gave Himself for your ransom,
Gave up His glory above;
Laid down His life without murmur,
You from sin's ruin to save;
Give Him your heart's adoration,
Give Him the best that you have."},{ID:35,
Text:"V4. THOU, MY EVERLASTING PORTION"},{
Text:"Thou, my everlasting portion,
More than friend or life to me;
All along my pilgrim journey,
Saviour, let me walk with Thee.
Close to Thee, close to Thee,
Close to Thee, close to Thee;
All along my pilgrim journey,
Saviour, let me walk with Thee."},{ID:2,
Text:"Not for ease or worldly pleasure,
Nor for fame my pray'r shall be;
Gladly will I toil and suffer,
Only let me walk with Thee.
Close to Thee, close to Thee,
Close to Thee, close to Thee;
Gladly will toil and suffer,
Only let me walk with Thee."},{ID:3,
Text:"Lead me thro' the vale of shadows,
Bear me o'er life's fitful sea;
Then the gate of life eternal
May I enter, Lord, with Thee.
Close to Thee, close to Thee,
Close to Thee, close to Thee;
Then the gate of life eternal
May I enter, Lord, with Thee."},{ID:35,
Text:"V5. HAVE THINE OWN WAY, LORD"},{ID:36,
Text:"I. Have Thine own way, Lord!
Have Thine own way!Thou art the potter,
I am the clay; Mold me and make me
After Thy will, while I am waiting,
Yielded and still."},{ID:2,
Text:"Have Thine own way, Lord!
Have Thine own way! Search me and try me,
Master, today! Whiter than snow Lord,
Wash me just now, As in Thy presence
Humbly I bow."},{ID:3,
Text:"Have Thine own way, Lord!
Have Thine -own way! Wounded and weary,
Help- me, I pray! Power all power
Surely is Thine! Touch me and heal me,
Saviour divine."},{ID:4,
Text:"Have Thine own way, Lord!
Have Thine own way! Hold o'er my being
Absolute sway! Fill with Thy Spirit
Till all shall see Christ only, always,
Living in me. Amen."},{ID:356,
Text:"TAKE MY LIFE, AND LET IT BE"},{
Text:"Take my life, and let it be
Consecrated, Lord, to Thee;
Take my hands and let them move
At the impulse of Thy love.
Lord I give my life to Thee,
Thine forever more to be;
Lord, I give my life to Thee,
Thine forevermore to be."},{ID:2,
Text:"Take my feet, and let them be
Swift and beautiful for Thee;
Take my voice and let me sing
Always, only, for my King."},{ID:3,
Text:"Take my silver and my gold,
Not a mite would I withhold; :
Take my moments and my days,
Let them flow in creaseless praise."},{ID:4,
Text:"Take my will, and make it Thine,
It shall be no longer mine;
Take my heart, it is Thine own,
It shall be Thy royal throne."},{ID:357,
Text:"TAKE MY LIFE, AND LET IT BE"},{
Text:"Take my life and let it be
Consecrated, Lord to Thee;
Take my hands and let them move
At the impulse of Thy love,
At the impulse of Thy love."},{ID:2,
Text:"Take my feet and let them be
Swift and beautiful for Thee;
Take my voice and let me sing
Always, only for my King,
Always, only, for my King."},{ID:3,
Text:"Take my silver and my gold,
Not a mite would I withhold;
Take my moments and my days,
Let them flow in ceaseless praise,
Let them flow in ceaseless praise."},{ID:4,
Text:"Take my will and make it Thine,
It shall be no longer mine;
Take my heart, it is Thine own,
It shall be Thy royal throne,
It shall be Thy royal throne. Amen."},{ID:358,
Text:"A CHARGE TO KEEP I HAVE"},{
Text:"A charge to keep I have,
A God to glorify,
Who gave His Son my soul to save,
And fit it for the sky."},{ID:2,
Text:"To serve the present age
My calling to fulfil;
O may it all my pow'rs engage
To do my Master's will!"},{ID:3,
Text:"Arm me with jealous care.
As in Thy sight to live;
And a Thy servant, Lord, prepare
A strict account to give. Amen."},{ID:35,
Text:"V9. I'LL LIVE FOR HIM"},{ID:36,
Text:"I. My life, my love I give to Thee,
Thou Lamb of God who died for me;
O may I ever faithful be,
My Saviour and my God!
I'II live for Him who died for me,
How happy then my life shall be!
I'll live for Him who died for me,
My Saviour and my God!"},{ID:2,
Text:"I now believe Thou dost receive,
For Thou hast died that I might live;
And now henceforth I'II trust in Thee,
My Saviour and my God!"},{ID:3,
Text:"O Thou who died on Calvary,
To save my soul and make me free,
I'II consecrate my life to Thee,
My Saviour and my God!"},{ID:360,
Text:"JESUS CALLS US O'ER THE TUMULT"},{
Text:"Jesus calls us o'er the tumult
Of our life's wild, restless sea;
Day by day His sweet voice soundeth,
Saying, \"Christian, follow me!\""},{ID:2,
Text:"Jesus calls us from the worship
Of the vain world's golden store,
From each idol that would keep us,
Saying, \"Christian, love me more.\""},{ID:3,
Text:"In our joys and in our sorrows,
Days of toil and hours of ease,
Still He calls, in cares1Il1d pleasures,
\"Christian, love me more than these.\""},{ID:4,
Text:"Jesus calls us: by Thy mercies,
Saviour, may we hear Thy call,
Give our hearts to Thine obedience,
Serve and love Thee best of all."},{ID:36,
Text:"V1. WHERE HE LEADS ME"},{ID:37,
Text:"I. I can hear my Saviour calling;
I can hear my Saviour calling,
I can hear my saviour calling,
\"Take thy cross and follow, follow me.\"
Where He leads me I will follow,
Where He leads me I will follow,
Where He leads me I will follow,
I'll go with Him, with Him all the way."},{ID:2,
Text:"I'll go with Him through the garden,
I'll go with Him through the garden,
I'll go with Him through the garden,
I'll go with Him, with Him all the way."},{ID:3,
Text:"I'll go with Him through the judgment,
I'll go with Him through the judgment,
I'll go with Him through the judgment,
I'll go with Him, with Him all the way."},{ID:4,
Text:"He will give me grace and glory,
He will give me grace and glory,
He will give me grace and glory,
And go with me, with me all the way."},{ID:362,
Text:"FOOTSTEPS OF JESUS"},{ID:363,
Text:"I. Sweetly, Lord, have we heard
Thee calling, \"Come, follow me!\"
And we see where Thy foot prints falling,
Lead us to Thee.
Footprints of Jesus that make the pathway glow;
We will follow the steps of
Jesus where 'er they go."},{ID:2,
Text:"Though they lead o'er the cold, dark mountains,
Seeking His sheep,
Or along by Siloam's fountains,
Helping the weak."},{ID:3,
Text:"If they lead thro' the temple holy,
Preaching the word,
Or in homes of the poor and lowly,
Serving the Lord."},{ID:4,
Text:"Then at last, when on high He sees us,
Our journey done,
We will rest where the steps of Jesus
End at His throne."},{ID:363,
Text:"I SURRENDER ALL"},{ID:364,
Text:"I. All to Jesus I surrender,
All to Him I freely give;
I will ever love and trust Him,
In His presence daily live.
I surrender all,
I surrender all;
All to Thee, my blessed Saviour,
I surrender all."},{ID:2,
Text:"All to Jesus I surrender,
Make me, Saviour, wholly Thine;
Let me feel the Holy Spirit
Truly know that Thou art mine."},{ID:3,
Text:"All to Jesus I surrender,
Lord, I give myself to thee;
Fill me with Thy love and power,
Let Thy blessing fall on me."},{ID:36,
Text:"V4. YIELD NOT TO TEMPTATION"},{ID:37,
Text:"I. Yield not to temptation,
For yielding is sin;
Each vict'ry will help you
Some other to win;
Fight manfully onward,
Dark passions subdue,
Look ever to Jesus,
He'll carry you through.
Ask the Saviour to help you,
Comfort, strengthen, and keep you;
He is willing to aid you,
He will carry you through."},{ID:2,
Text:"Shun evil companions,
Bad language disdain,
God's name hold in rev'rence,
Nor take it in vain;
Be thoughtful and earnest,
Kind hearted and true,
Look ever to Jesus,
He'll carry you through."},{ID:3,
Text:"To him that o'er cometh
God giveth a crown,
Thro' faith we shall conquer,
Tho' often cast down;
He, who is our Saviour,
Our strength will renew,
Look ever to Jesus,
He'll carry you through."},{ID:36,
Text:"V5. OH, FOR A CLOSER WALK"},{
Text:"Oh, for a closer walk with God,
A calm and heav'nly frame,
A light to shine upon the road
That leads me to the Lamb!"},{ID:2,
Text:"Where is the blessedness I knew
When first I saw the Lord?
Where is the soul refreshing view
Of Jesus and His Word?"},{ID:3,
Text:"What peaceful hours I then enjoyed!
How sweet their mem'ry still!
But they have left an aching void
The world can never fill."},{ID:4,
Text:"Return, 0 Holy Dove, return,
Sweet messenger of rest;
I hate the sins that made Thee mourn,
And drove Thee from my breast. Amen."},{ID:36,
Text:"V6. BLEST BE THE TIE"},{ID:37,
Text:"I. Blest be the tie that binds
Our hearts in Christian love;
The fellowship of kindred minds
Is like to that above"},{ID:2,
Text:"Before our Father's throne
We pour our ardent pray'rs;
Our fears, our hopes, our aims are one,
Our comforts and our cares."},{ID:3,
Text:"We share our mutual woes,
Our mutual burdens bear;
And often for each other flows
The sympathizing tear."},{ID:4,
Text:"When we asunder part,
It gives us inward pain;
But we shall still be joined in heart,
And hope to meet again. Amen."},{ID:36,
Text:"V7. TAKE TIME TO BE HOLY"},{ID:37,
Text:"I. Take time to be holy,
Speak oft with thy Lord;
Abide in Him always,
And feed on His Word:
Make friends of God's children,
Help those who are weak;
Forgetting in nothing
His blessing to seek."},{ID:2,
Text:"Take time to be holy,
The world rushes on;
Spend much time in secret
With Jesus alone:
By looking to Jesus
Like Him thou shalt be;
Thy friends in thy conduct
His likeness shall see."},{ID:3,
Text:"Take time to be holy,
Let Him be thy guide,
And run not before Him
Whatever betide;
In joy or in sorrow
Still follow thy Lord,
And looking to Jesus,
Still trust in His Word."},{ID:4,
Text:"Take time to be holy,
Be calm in thy soul;
Each tho't and each motive
Beneath His control;
Thus led by His Spirit
To fountains of love,
Thou soon shalt be fitted
For service above."},{ID:36,
Text:"V8. BRETHREN, WE HAVE MET TO WORSHIP"},{ID:37,
Text:"I. Brethren, we have met to worship
And adore the Lord our God;
Will you pray with all your power,
While we try to preach the Word?
All is vain unless the Spirit
Of the Holy One comes down;
Brethren, pray, and holy manna
Will be showered all around."},{ID:2,
Text:"Brethren, see poor sinners round you
Slumbering on the brink of woe;
Death is coming, hell is moving,
Can you bear to let them go?
See our fathers and mothers,
And our children sinking down;
Brethren, pray, and holy manna
Will be showered all around."},{ID:3,
Text:"Sisters, will you join and help us?
Moses' sister aided him;
Will you help the trembling mourners
Who are struggling hard with sin?
Tell them all about the Saviour,
Tell them that He will be found;
Sisters, pray, and holy manna
Will be showered all around."},{ID:4,
Text:"Let us love our God supremely,
Let us love each other too;
Let us love and pray for sinners,
Till our God makes all things new.
Then He'll call us home to heaven.
At His table we'll sit down;
Christ will gird Himself, and serve us
With sweet manna all around."},{ID:36,
Text:"V9. PURER IN HEART, 0 GOD"},{ID:37,
Text:"I. Purer in heart, 0 God, Help me to be;
May I devote my life Wholly to Thee:
Watch Thou my wayward feet,
Guide me with counsel sweet;
Purer in heart Help me to be."},{ID:2,
Text:"Purer in heart, 0 God, Help me to be;
Teach me to do Thy will most lovingly:
Be Thou my friend and guide,
Let me with Thee abide;
Purer in heart Help me to be."},{ID:3,
Text:"Purer in heart, 0 God, Help me to be,
Unit! Thy holy face One day I see:
Keep me from secret sin,
Reign Thou my soul within;
Purer in heart Help me to be. Amen."},{ID:370,
Text:"WALK IN THE LIGHT"},{ID:371,
Text:"I. Walk in the light! So shalt thou know
That fellowship of love
His Spirit only can bestow,
Who reigns in light above."},{ID:2,
Text:"Walk in the light! and thou shalt find
Thy heart made truly His,
Who dwells in cloudless light enshrined,
In whom no darkness is."},{ID:3,
Text:"Walk in the light! and thou shalt own
Thy darkness passed away,
Because that light hath on thee shone,
In which is perfect day."},{ID:4,
Text:"Walk in the light! and thine shall be
A path, though thorny, bright:
For God, by grace shall dwell in thee,
And God Himself is light. Amen"},{ID:37,
Text:"V1. LEANING ON THE EVERLASTING ARMS"},{ID:38,
Text:"I. What a fellowship, what a joy divine,
Leaning on the everlasting arms;
What blessedness, what a peace is mine,
Leaning on the everlasting arms.
Leaning, leaning,
Safe and secure from all alarms;
Leaning, leaning,
Leaning on the everlasting arms."},{ID:2,
Text:"Oh, how sweet to walk in this pilgrim way,
Leaning on the everlasting arms;
Oh, how bright the path grows from day to day,
Leaning on the everlasting arms."},{ID:3,
Text:"What have I to dread, what have
I to fear,
Leaning on the everlasting arms?
I have blessed peace with my
Lord so near,
Leaning on the everlasting arms."},{ID:37,
Text:"V2. GOD BE WITH YOU"},{ID:38,
Text:"I. God be with you till we meet again!
By His counsels guide, uphold you,
With His sheep securely fold you:
God be with you till we meet again!
Till we meet! Till we meet!
Till we meet at Jesus' feet;
Till we meet! Till we meet!
God be with you till we meet again."},{ID:2,
Text:"God be with you till we meet again!
'Neath His wings securely hide you,
Daily manna still provide you;
God be with you till we meet again!"},{ID:3,
Text:"God be with you till we meet again!
Keep love's banner floating o'er you,
Smite death's threat'ning wave before you;
God be with you till we meet again!"},{ID:37,
Text:"V3. 0 HAPPY HOME WHERE THOU ART LOVED"},{ID:38,
Text:"<fCalibri><s846>I. O happy home where Thou art loved the dearest,
</s></f>Thou loving friend, and Saviour of our race,
And where arnong the guests there never cometh
One who can hold such high and honored place"},{ID:2,
Text:"O happy home where each one serves Thee, lowly,
Whatever his appointed work may be,
Till every common task seems great and holy,
When it is done, O Lord, as unto Thee."},{ID:3,
Text:"O happy home where Thou art not forgotten
When joy is over flowing, full, and free;
O happy home where every wounded spirit
Is brought, Physician, Comforter, to Thee."},{ID:4,
Text:"Until at last, when earthly work is ended,
All meet Thee in the blessed home above
From whence Thou earnest,
Where Thou hast ascended,
Thy everlasting home of peace and love. Amen."}]},{ID:362,Guid:"iG7ExgTj20aeLPWx9/DTbQ",Verses:[{
Text:"362	FOOTSTEPS OF JESUS"},{ID:2,
Text:"V. Sweetly, Lord, have we heard
Thee calling, \"Come, follow me!\"
And we see where Thy foot prints falling,
Lead us to Thee."},{ID:3,
Text:"Footprints of Jesus that make the pathway glow;
We will follow the steps of
Jesus where 'er they go."},{ID:3,
Text:"v. Though they lead o'er the cold, dark mountains,
Seeking His sheep,
Or along by Siloam's fountains,
Helping the weak."},{ID:4,
Text:"Footprints of Jesus that make the pathway glow;
We will follow the steps of
Jesus where 'er they go."},{ID:3,
Text:"if they lead through the temple holy
Preaching the word,
Or in homes of the poor and lowly,
Serving the Lord."},{ID:4,
Text:"Footprints of Jesus that make the pathway glow;
We will follow the steps of
Jesus where 'er they go."},{ID:4,
Text:"Then at last when on high he sees us
Our journey done,
We will rest where the steps of Jesus
End at His throne."},{ID:5,
Text:"Footprints of Jesus that make the pathway glow;
We will follow the steps of
Jesus where 'er they go."}],Style:{Body:{FontSize:150,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1}},
Text:"BH 362 FOOTSTEPS OF JESUS
"},{ID:374,Guid:"GrikfSkBF02qtqy9orEbLQ",Verses:[{Style:{Body:{FontStyle:{Fill:{Color:"FFF4F1E3"},Stroke:{Color:"FF225BA1"},ShadowColor:"FF8C8C8C",ShadowRadius:33,ShadowDirection:-45,ShadowDepth:21}},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"Happy the home when God is there,
And love fills every <s1076>breast</s>;
When one their wish, and one their prayer,
And one their heavenly rest."},{ID:2,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1,FontStyle:{Fill:{Color:"FFF4F1E3"},Stroke:{Color:"FF225BA1"},ShadowColor:"FF8C8C8C",ShadowRadius:33,ShadowDirection:-45,ShadowDepth:21}}},
Text:"name
Is sweet to every ear;
Where children early lisp His fame,
And parents hold Him dear."},{ID:3,Style:{Body:{FontStyle:{Fill:{Color:"FFF4F1E3"},Stroke:{Color:"FF225BA1"},ShadowColor:"FF8C8C8C",ShadowRadius:33,ShadowDirection:-45,ShadowDepth:21}}},
Text:"Happy the home where prayHappy the home where Jesus' er is heard,
And praise is wont to rise;
Where parents love the sacred Word
And all its wisdom prize."},{ID:4,Style:{Body:{FontStyle:{Fill:{Color:"FFF4F1E3"},Stroke:{Color:"FF225BA1"},ShadowColor:"FF8C8C8C",ShadowRadius:33,ShadowDirection:-45,ShadowDepth:21}},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"Lord let us in our homes agree
This blessed peace to gain;
Unite our hearts in love to thee,
And love to all will reign. Amen"}],Style:{Body:{Wrap:1}},
Text:"BH374 - HAPPY THE HOME WHEN GOD IS THERE"},{ID:375,Guid:"t6RsHvYz3UqCgPoovbWXJA",Verses:[{
Text:"O Thou whose gracious presence blest
The home at Bethany,
This shelter from the world's unrest,
This home made ready for its Guest,
We dedicate to Thee."},{ID:2,
Text:"When Thou didst pass the Temple gate,
To pray beneath its dome,
It was Thy Father's house, more
Because by love made.
It was Thine only home."},{ID:3,
Text:"We build an altar here, and pray
That Thou wilt show Thy face,
Dear Lord, if Thou wilt come to stay,
This home we consecrate today
Will be a holy place. Amen."},{ID:37,
Text:"V6. FRIEND OF THE HOME"},{
Text:"Friend of the home, as when in Galilee,
The mothers brought their little ones to Thee,
So we, dear Lord, would now the children bring,
And seek for them the shelter of Thy wing."},{ID:2,
Text:"Lord may Thy church, as with a mother's care,
For Thee the lambs within he bossom bear;
And grant, as morning grows to noon, that they
Still in her love and holy service stay."},{ID:3,
Text:"Draw, through the child, the parents nearer Thee,
Endue their home with growing sanctity;
And gather all, by earthly homes made one,
In heaven, o Christ, when earthly days are done. Amen."}],
Text:"O THOU WHOSE GRACIOUS PRESENCE BLEST"},{ID:377,Guid:"lXnA6PJ4IU2XpwlB7Axvbw",Verses:[{Style:{Body:{FontName:"Arial Rounded MT Bold",FontSize:500,TextAlignment:2,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"},Luminosity:-70}},
Text:"God, give us Christian homes!
Homes where the Bible is loved and taught,"},{ID:2,Style:{Body:{FontName:"Arial Rounded MT Bold",FontSize:500,TextAlignment:2,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"},Luminosity:-70}},
Text:"Homes where the Master's will is sought,
<s1076>Homes crowned with beauty Thy love hath wrought;</s>"},{Tag:1,ID:0,Style:{Body:{FontName:"Arial Rounded MT Bold",FontSize:500,TextAlignment:2,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes; 
God, give us Christian home!</s>"},{ID:2,Style:{Body:{FontName:"Arial Rounded MT Bold",FontSize:500,TextAlignment:2,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes!
Homes where the father is true and strong,</s>"},{ID:3,Style:{Body:{FontName:"Arial Rounded MT Bold",FontSize:500,TextAlignment:2,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>Homes that are free from the blight of wrong,
Homes that are joyous with love and song;</s>"},{ID:3,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes;
God, give us Christian homes!</s>"},{ID:3,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes!
Homes where the mother, in queenly quest,</s>"},{ID:4,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>Strives to show others Thy way is best,
Homes where the Lord is an honored guest;</s>"},{ID:4,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes;
God, give us Christian homes!</s>"},{ID:4,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"},Luminosity:-85}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes!
Homes where the children are led to know</s>"},{ID:5,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>Christ in His beauty who loves them so,
Homes where the altar fires burn and glow;</s>"},{ID:5,Style:{Body:{Wrap:1,FontStyle:{Fill:{Color:"FFF4F1E3"},Stroke:{Color:"FF225BA1"},ShadowColor:"FF8C8C8C",ShadowRadius:33,ShadowDirection:-45,ShadowDepth:21}},Background:{Brush:{Color:"FF000000"}}},
Text:"<s1076>God, give us Christian homes;
God, give us Christian homes! Amen</s>"}],Style:{Body:{Wrap:1}},
Text:"BH 377 - GOD, GIVE US CHRISTIAN HOMES!"},{ID:382,Guid:"7eeIYJ/8sk2Vde63rtWUow",Verses:[{
Text:"382. I LOVE THY KINGDOM, LORD"},{
Text:"I  love Thy kingdom, Lord,
The house of Thine abode,
The church our blest Redeemer saved
With His own precious blood."},{ID:2,
Text:"I love Thy church, O God!
Her walls before Thee stand,
Dear as the apple of Thine eye,
And graven on Thy hand."},{ID:3,
Text:" For her my tears shall fall;
For her my pray'rs ascend;
To her my cares and toils be giv'n,
Till toils and cares shall end."},{ID:4,
Text:" Beyond my highest joy
I prize her heav'nly ways,
Her sweet communion solemn vows,
Her hymns of love and praise."},{ID:5,
Text:"Sure as Thy truth shall last,
To Zion shall be giv'n
The brightest glories earth can yield,
And brighter bliss of heav'n. Amen."}],
Text:"BH 382. I LOVE THY KINGDOM, LORD
"},{ID:445,Guid:"6aojFLtEuUqWE6XliDob0Q",Verses:[{
Text:"Rise up, O men of God!
Have done with lesser things;
Give heart and soul and mind and strength
To serve the King of kings."},{ID:2,
Text:"Rise up, O men of God!
His kingdom tarries long;
Bring in the day of brotherhood,
And end the night of wrong."},{ID:3,
Text:"Rise up, O men of God!
The Church for you doth wait,
Her strength unequal to her task;
Rise up and make her great."},{ID:4,
Text:"Lift high the cross of Christ;
Tread where His feet have trod;
As brothers of the Son of man,
Rise up, O men of God!"}],
Text:"BH 445 Rise up, O men of God!
"},{ID:501,Guid:"hhkxo/r/KkeXq6ItSBvLxg",Verses:[{
Text:"O PERFECT LOVE
1. O perfect Love, all human thought transcending,
Lowly we kneel in prayer before thy throne
That theirs may be the love which knows no ending
Whom thou forever more dost join in one"},{ID:2,
Text:"O perfect life, be thou their full assurance
Of tender charity and steadfast faith
Of perfect hope and quiet,brave endurance
With child like trust that fears no pain nor death"},{ID:3,
Text:"Grant them the joy which brightens earthly sorrow
Grant them the peace which calms all earthly strife
And to life's day the glorious unknown morrow
That dawns upon eternal love and life. Amen"}],
Text:"BH 501 O PERFECT LOVE"},{ID:509,Guid:"07y5Yz6GuEmMilqwoQYaWw",Verses:[{
Text:"I am so glad that our Father in heaven
Tells of His love in the Book He has given
Wonderful things in the bible I see
This is the dearest that Jesus loves me"},{ID:2,
Text:"I am so gladthat Jesus loves me
Jesus loves me, Jesus loves me
I am so glad that Jesus loves me
Jesus loves even me"},{ID:3,
Text:"Tho' i forget Him and wander away 
Kindly He follows wherever i stray
Back to His dear loving arms would i flee
when i remember that Jesus loves me"},{ID:4,
Text:"Oh, if there is only one song i can sing 
when in His beauty i see the great king
this shall my siong in eternity be
Oh what a wonder that Jesus loves me"}],
Text:"BH 509 I AM SO GLAD THAT OUR FATHER"}],IsCompressed:0,Guid:"4oMF45lkQU+iQKNYdsgROA",Style:{Body:{FontSize:150,CaseType:0,TextAlignment:2,VerticalAlignment:1,Wrap:1,Transition:4,FontStyle:{Fill:{Color:"FFF4F1E3"},Stroke:{Color:"FF225BA1"},ShadowColor:"FF8C8C8C",ShadowRadius:33,ShadowDirection:-45,ShadowDepth:21}},Background:{Video:"hpm_christmas snow.SD480.wmv"}},
Text:"Baptist Hymnal "}